WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:01:21.831 --> 00:01:24.138
Sadhguru: Good afternoon everybody,

00:01:24.138 --> 00:01:27.597
the Excellencies and Ladies and Gentlemen.

00:01:27.597 --> 00:01:31.763
Thank you for being here.

00:01:31.763 --> 00:01:33.924
Maxwell Kennedy: Good afternoon Sadhguru

00:01:33.924 --> 00:01:38.103
and good afternoon to your Excellencies and distinguished guests

00:01:38.103 --> 00:01:42.406
and to all the meditators who are watching on the internet right now.

00:01:42.406 --> 00:01:44.911
I’m so grateful to be here

00:01:44.911 --> 00:01:48.379
and it's such a privilege really to be here.

00:01:48.379 --> 00:01:49.883
My name is Maxwell Kennedy

00:01:49.883 --> 00:01:51.585
and I’ve been…

00:01:51.585 --> 00:01:55.861
I learned how to meditate from Sadhguru a few years ago

00:01:55.861 --> 00:01:58.888
So, we are here at the United Nations

00:01:58.888 --> 00:02:02.832
and there are fort… maybe forty or sixty ambassadors here

00:02:02.832 --> 00:02:04.353
and seventy different countries

00:02:04.353 --> 00:02:06.402
and 7000 people

00:02:06.402 --> 00:02:09.424
and we are here to talk about Sustainable Development.

00:02:09.424 --> 00:02:13.133
So, why did you start with a chant?

00:02:15.683 --> 00:02:18.493
Sadhguru: (Laughs) The chant is an invocation.

00:02:18.493 --> 00:02:21.738
An invocation means -

00:02:21.738 --> 00:02:27.130
to perform different types of activities,

00:02:27.130 --> 00:02:30.171
we need to have our energies in different ways,

00:02:30.171 --> 00:02:31.603
otherwise…

00:02:31.603 --> 00:02:35.824
Most people have become competent in one way or the other

00:02:35.824 --> 00:02:38.437
but if you ask them to do something totally different,

00:02:38.437 --> 00:02:41.532
they will find themselves totally at loss.

00:02:41.532 --> 00:02:46.477
This is simply because their energies get directed in one way only.

00:02:46.477 --> 00:02:50.263
An invocation means you, kind of,

00:02:50.263 --> 00:02:54.336
make yourself malleable in such a way that for every different type of action,

00:02:54.336 --> 00:02:58.643
you need your energies in different parts of your system

00:02:58.643 --> 00:03:00.959
and you’re able to graduate that,

00:03:00.959 --> 00:03:04.987
calibrate that in such a way to perform that specific activity.

00:03:04.987 --> 00:03:06.729
So, when I sit here,

00:03:06.729 --> 00:03:12.008
what we need to do is different from what I was doing when I was walking down here.

00:03:12.008 --> 00:03:14.405
So, this is just calibration using sounds.

00:03:14.405 --> 00:03:16.466
If we have to know the meaning,

00:03:16.466 --> 00:03:18.466
it's talking about

00:03:18.466 --> 00:03:21.271
how birth is sweetness

00:03:21.271 --> 00:03:23.200
but death is compassion;

00:03:23.200 --> 00:03:24.435
it's a relief.

00:03:24.435 --> 00:03:29.737
We may think death is a terrible thing but aren’t we glad that someday we will die.

00:03:29.737 --> 00:03:34.095
Suppose we could not die, that would be terrible, isn't it (Laughs)?

00:03:34.095 --> 00:03:35.953
Suppose we can't die at all!

00:03:35.953 --> 00:03:40.613
And above all, it is talking about yoga in the sense,

00:03:40.613 --> 00:03:45.896
the chant is describing yoga as a way of transcending time.

00:03:45.896 --> 00:03:48.398
When we say transcending time,

00:03:48.398 --> 00:03:53.031
right now we have a sense of time only because

00:03:53.031 --> 00:03:56.363
we are so identified with our physical nature.

00:03:56.363 --> 00:03:58.174
Suppose we did not have a body,

00:03:58.174 --> 00:04:00.897
we would ha… would not have any sense of time.

00:04:00.897 --> 00:04:02.559
Our body is keeping time.

00:04:02.559 --> 00:04:05.005
Everything that is time, is cyclical

00:04:05.005 --> 00:04:08.758
but yoga is a dimension which wants to transcend,

00:04:08.758 --> 00:04:11.094
which helps you to transcend these cycles

00:04:11.094 --> 00:04:14.705
and make a journey beyond cyclical nature of life

00:04:14.705 --> 00:04:18.742
which is the nature of physical existence.

00:04:18.742 --> 00:04:20.089
Maxwell Kennedy: Thank you.

00:04:20.089 --> 00:04:23.645
I had a teacher at Harvard,

00:04:23.645 --> 00:04:25.713
who was a medical doctor.

00:04:25.713 --> 00:04:27.442
And he told me a story, that

00:04:27.442 --> 00:04:30.239
when he was a young doctor he went down to Mississippi

00:04:30.239 --> 00:04:32.992
and he saw children there in the United States -

00:04:32.992 --> 00:04:35.817
this is in the mid 1960’s - who were starving.

00:04:35.817 --> 00:04:39.873
And after that trip he went to Washington DC

00:04:39.873 --> 00:04:43.105
and he had… he tried to meet a group of senators

00:04:43.105 --> 00:04:46.297
and he went to one after another and none of them would talk to him.

00:04:46.297 --> 00:04:50.955
And on Sunday afternoon he got my father’s phone number at home.

00:04:50.955 --> 00:04:52.855
My father is Senator Robert F. Kennedy

00:04:52.855 --> 00:04:56.725
and my sister Kerry who runs the Robert F. Kennedy Memorial is here right now

00:04:56.725 --> 00:04:58.716
and my wife Vicki.

00:04:58.716 --> 00:05:01.539
So… But he got my dad’s number and he called

00:05:01.539 --> 00:05:04.647
and it was Sunday my dad’s with children

00:05:04.647 --> 00:05:08.788
and he said to him, “Well, all right, why don’t you come over and we’ll talk.”

00:05:08.788 --> 00:05:12.634
And after they spoke, my dad went to Mississippi

00:05:12.634 --> 00:05:15.363
to where this doctor had gone

00:05:15.363 --> 00:05:19.757
and when he came back he wrote this… he said these words,

00:05:19.757 --> 00:05:22.456
“…and there are others...

00:05:22.456 --> 00:05:26.742
“On the back roads of Mississippi where thousands of children

00:05:26.742 --> 00:05:29.025
slowly starve their lives away.

00:05:29.025 --> 00:05:33.565
Their minds damaged beyond repair by the age of four or five,

00:05:33.565 --> 00:05:35.775
in the camps of the migrant workers,

00:05:35.775 --> 00:05:39.951
a half a million nomads virtually unprotected by collective bargaining

00:05:39.951 --> 00:05:43.167
or social security, minimum wage or workmen’s compensation.

00:05:43.167 --> 00:05:48.182
Exposed to the caprice of fate and the cruelty of the fellowmen alike

00:05:48.182 --> 00:05:52.398
and on Indian reservations where the unemployment rate is eighty percent,

00:05:52.398 --> 00:05:55.380
and where suicide is not a philosopher’s question

00:05:55.380 --> 00:06:00.248
but the leading cause of death among young people.”

00:06:00.248 --> 00:06:01.976
So, after that trip,

00:06:01.976 --> 00:06:03.346
my father went back to the Senate

00:06:03.346 --> 00:06:05.470
and he worked with a group of others

00:06:05.470 --> 00:06:09.384
and they created the first food stamps program in the United States

00:06:09.384 --> 00:06:14.417
and that is kind of the development model that I’m used to.

00:06:14.417 --> 00:06:19.156
So, when I look at the Sustainable Development Goals of the United Nations,

00:06:19.156 --> 00:06:21.223
my immediate reaction is to think

00:06:21.223 --> 00:06:24.917
are the Addis Ababa accords going to fund this or not?

00:06:24.917 --> 00:06:28.192
But you have a different approach.

00:06:28.192 --> 00:06:31.638
Can you talk about yoga in that context?

00:06:33.618 --> 00:06:37.004
Sadhguru: So, when we say Sustainable Development Goals

00:06:37.004 --> 00:06:40.140
we are talking about human well-being,

00:06:40.140 --> 00:06:44.802
addressing human well-being as seventeen different issues

00:06:44.802 --> 00:06:49.979
which concerns poverty, nourishment, health, women’s issues, environment,

00:06:49.979 --> 00:06:52.310
these kind of things.

00:06:52.310 --> 00:06:56.221
Essentially, we’re talking about human well-being.

00:06:56.221 --> 00:07:01.832
How can you transform the world without transforming individual human beings?

00:07:01.832 --> 00:07:04.974
This is the effort that’s going on in the world for a long time.

00:07:04.974 --> 00:07:07.616
We want to transform the world

00:07:07.616 --> 00:07:10.718
but we are not aiming at individual human beings.

00:07:10.718 --> 00:07:12.852
The world is just a word -

00:07:12.852 --> 00:07:15.132
it is just you and me.

00:07:15.132 --> 00:07:18.168
If there is no transformation in you and me,

00:07:18.168 --> 00:07:21.562
if there is no change in the way we perceive,

00:07:21.562 --> 00:07:24.926
experience and fee… think, feel and act in this world,

00:07:24.926 --> 00:07:27.357
how can you change the world?

00:07:27.357 --> 00:07:29.315
So, we can pump in money,

00:07:29.315 --> 00:07:30.541
we can have projects,

00:07:30.541 --> 00:07:32.753
they will all go up and go down.

00:07:32.753 --> 00:07:37.331
But only if we transform individual human beings on a large scale

00:07:37.331 --> 00:07:39.275
only then there’ll be true transformation.

00:07:39.275 --> 00:07:42.214
This is why yoga becomes a significant thing.

00:07:42.214 --> 00:07:46.381
Today, the United Nations taking this up…

00:07:46.381 --> 00:07:50.081
taking up this International Yoga Day is a very important step.

00:07:50.081 --> 00:07:52.384
I would say it's a revolutionary approach

00:07:52.384 --> 00:07:56.251
because without transforming individual human beings,

00:07:56.251 --> 00:07:58.570
you cannot really transform the world because

00:07:58.570 --> 00:08:00.134
there is no such thing as -

00:08:00.134 --> 00:08:04.640
in reality. In reality there’s just you, me and someone else.

00:08:04.640 --> 00:08:06.873
If all of us change, the world has changed.

00:08:06.873 --> 00:08:09.566
If we refuse to change, we will be only talking about it.

00:08:09.566 --> 00:08:13.681
I’ve been to any number of International Peace Conferences

00:08:13.681 --> 00:08:16.337
and everybody is talking about world peace.

00:08:16.337 --> 00:08:21.442
In one of these conferences where there were over seventeen Nobel Laureates,

00:08:21.442 --> 00:08:23.734
I asked them a simple question,

00:08:23.734 --> 00:08:27.589
“Is it… Is it true that all of you are truly peaceful human beings?

00:08:27.589 --> 00:08:29.210
Can you put your hand on your heart and say

00:08:29.210 --> 00:08:30.416
‘I’m peaceful’?”

00:08:30.416 --> 00:08:34.691
They admitted, “No Sadhguru, we don’t know how to be peaceful.

00:08:34.691 --> 00:08:36.503
But we want the world peaceful.”

00:08:36.503 --> 00:08:38.921
How is that possible?

00:08:38.921 --> 00:08:44.504
What… What you see as the world is just a larger manifestation of who we are.

00:08:44.504 --> 00:08:48.071
Maxwell Kennedy: Sadhguru, You can see all around the world in Brazil,

00:08:48.071 --> 00:08:50.307
in the United States, in L.A. where I live,

00:08:50.307 --> 00:08:51.993
people are doing yoga.

00:08:51.993 --> 00:08:56.204
And when we’re doing it, I’m stretching out my body (Sadhguru laughs)

00:08:56.204 --> 00:08:59.020
and trying to control my breathing.

00:08:59.020 --> 00:09:02.361
Can you explain what yoga really is

00:09:02.361 --> 00:09:08.140
and how that can help attain the SDGs?

00:09:08.140 --> 00:09:12.330
Sadhguru: See, this fundamental human longing for health,

00:09:12.330 --> 00:09:14.260
for well-being,

00:09:14.260 --> 00:09:16.950
for fulfillment of life,

00:09:16.950 --> 00:09:23.833
when you find a logically correct and scientifically ascertainable way,

00:09:23.833 --> 00:09:26.640
then we say this is yoga.

00:09:26.640 --> 00:09:28.274
Yoga means -

00:09:28.274 --> 00:09:30.858
in search… in pursuit of human well-being,

00:09:30.858 --> 00:09:32.596
we’ve been doing all kinds of things.

00:09:32.596 --> 00:09:33.909
We’ve been looking up for a long time,

00:09:33.909 --> 00:09:39.071
which has led to humanity being divided in the name of religions,

00:09:39.071 --> 00:09:40.732
castes, creeds,

00:09:40.732 --> 00:09:42.467
in so many different ways.

00:09:42.467 --> 00:09:45.567
Now in the last fifty years, I would say,

00:09:45.567 --> 00:09:50.607
we are looking out seriously and we are ripping the planet apart.

00:09:50.607 --> 00:09:53.448
All the environmental degradation that we’re talking about

00:09:53.448 --> 00:09:56.594
is just in pursuit of human well-being.

00:09:56.594 --> 00:09:58.029
In the last hundred years,

00:09:58.029 --> 00:10:02.627
definitely we are the most comfortable generation ever.

00:10:02.627 --> 00:10:07.042
But we cannot say we are well because (Laughs)

00:10:07.042 --> 00:10:08.726
we are not really well.

00:10:08.726 --> 00:10:10.952
People are not happy, people are not peaceful,

00:10:10.952 --> 00:10:14.523
that is not happening because we have not addressed the inner nature.

00:10:14.523 --> 00:10:17.942
So when it… when you address it in a scientific manner

00:10:17.942 --> 00:10:20.934
rather than by belief,

00:10:20.934 --> 00:10:22.251
by philosophy,

00:10:22.251 --> 00:10:23.602
by ideologies,

00:10:23.602 --> 00:10:26.615
you address human well-being in a scientific way -

00:10:26.615 --> 00:10:27.808
this is yoga.

00:10:27.808 --> 00:10:30.884
The word yoga literally means union.

00:10:30.884 --> 00:10:34.012
When we say union, what we’re talking about is,

00:10:34.012 --> 00:10:35.369
we’re talking about

00:10:35.369 --> 00:10:44.594
a scientific way of obliterating your… the boundaries of your individuality.

00:10:44.594 --> 00:10:47.748
When I say a scientific way of obliterating,

00:10:47.748 --> 00:10:50.230
the boundaries of your individual nature,

00:10:50.230 --> 00:10:51.695
what this means is –

00:10:51.695 --> 00:10:55.998
right now as we sit here, this is me, that is you, distinctly clear

00:10:55.998 --> 00:10:58.309
but we are breathing the same air,

00:10:58.309 --> 00:11:01.183
we are… we are a product of the same earth.

00:11:01.183 --> 00:11:05.679
What you call as myself is just a pop up on this planet and it’ll pop out.

00:11:05.679 --> 00:11:11.022
But in this little bit of time, we have divided this in such a way that we can't meet.

00:11:11.022 --> 00:11:15.791
Yoga means you obliterate this individual boundaries

00:11:15.791 --> 00:11:17.393
not intellectually,

00:11:17.393 --> 00:11:18.685
not by belief,

00:11:18.685 --> 00:11:21.935
not by ideology but as a living experience.

00:11:21.935 --> 00:11:26.176
We launched a… I mean this (Laughs) was there on the video -

00:11:26.176 --> 00:11:32.649
we launched a very large-scale environmental project in Southern India.

00:11:32.649 --> 00:11:35.057
The fundamental for this came from this.

00:11:35.057 --> 00:11:38.220
This happened to me when I was in the university

00:11:38.220 --> 00:11:40.532
and recently about eight years ago

00:11:40.532 --> 00:11:43.885
when I... when I happened to be in my hometown

00:11:43.885 --> 00:11:46.130
and after a very long time

00:11:46.130 --> 00:11:49.007
one of my English teachers came up to me and said,

00:11:49.007 --> 00:11:53.089
“Now I understand why you would not let me teach Robert Frost.”

00:11:53.089 --> 00:11:55.821
I said, “Ma’am, why would I not let you teach Robert Frost?

00:11:55.821 --> 00:11:57.307
I like Robert Frost.”

00:11:57.307 --> 00:12:00.869
She said, “Don’t you remember, you didn’t let me teach Frost.”

00:12:00.869 --> 00:12:01.962
Then I remembered,

00:12:01.962 --> 00:12:05.295
she came one day - till then we were reading only English poets -

00:12:05.295 --> 00:12:08.464
she came and introduced the American poet

00:12:08.464 --> 00:12:11.121
and she said, “Robert Frost, such a great man.”

00:12:11.121 --> 00:12:13.111
And then she started off

00:12:13.111 --> 00:12:15.647
“Woods are lovely dark and deep.”

00:12:15.647 --> 00:12:17.356
I said, “Stop!”

00:12:17.356 --> 00:12:21.958
I said, “A man who calls a tree a wood, I don’t want to listen to this guy.”

00:12:21.958 --> 00:12:26.099
She (Laughs)… She said, “No, no, this’s a very great poet.”

00:12:26.099 --> 00:12:28.499
I said, “I don’t care how great he is.

00:12:28.499 --> 00:12:31.964
He calls tree a wood.

00:12:31.964 --> 00:12:34.867
I don’t want to listen to him” (Laughs).

00:12:34.867 --> 00:12:38.897
Then, when we wanted to start this process in Southern India,

00:12:38.897 --> 00:12:41.558
when we found that rivers were going dry

00:12:41.558 --> 00:12:44.232
and the ground water was sinking very rapidly,

00:12:44.232 --> 00:12:49.021
when I decided we will plant 114 million trees in Tamil Nadu,

00:12:49.021 --> 00:12:51.546
the simple thing that we did was -

00:12:51.546 --> 00:12:54.815
I took thousands of people, made them sit under trees

00:12:54.815 --> 00:12:57.368
and we set up a yogic process with which

00:12:57.368 --> 00:13:01.936
they experienced that what they are breathing out,

00:13:01.936 --> 00:13:03.969
the trees are inhaling,

00:13:03.969 --> 00:13:06.118
what the trees are exhaling, they are inhaling.

00:13:06.118 --> 00:13:10.471
And they realized one half of their lungs is hanging out there.

00:13:10.471 --> 00:13:12.521
Once they realize this, there is no stopping.

00:13:12.521 --> 00:13:16.673
Even today millions of trees are being planted on a yearly basis,

00:13:16.673 --> 00:13:18.788
all done by common people.

00:13:18.788 --> 00:13:22.126
Simply because we brought this yogic experience to them

00:13:22.126 --> 00:13:26.016
that they truly realized that one half of their breathing apparatus

00:13:26.016 --> 00:13:28.306
is actually out there, not here.

00:13:28.306 --> 00:13:31.892
So, bringing this experience into people

00:13:31.892 --> 00:13:37.220
that what you think as myself is not within the boundaries of your physical nature,

00:13:37.220 --> 00:13:39.132
it goes well beyond that,

00:13:39.132 --> 00:13:43.674
if this becomes a living reality, then fulfilling these goals

00:13:43.674 --> 00:13:46.542
that United Nations has for the world is…

00:13:46.542 --> 00:13:51.065
becomes much more possible than the way it is right now,

00:13:51.065 --> 00:13:53.957
where we are trying to push in one way

00:13:53.957 --> 00:13:57.580
but a whole lot of people are pushing in the opposite direction

00:13:57.580 --> 00:14:00.710
because they don’t even see it as theirs.

00:14:00.710 --> 00:14:02.851
Maxwell Kennedy: Thank you Sadhguru.

00:14:02.851 --> 00:14:08.059
I wanted to point out this incredible thing about the tree planting project is that

00:14:08.059 --> 00:14:12.932
Sadhguru insisted that the trees be planted on small plots of land,

00:14:12.932 --> 00:14:14.159
less than half an acre

00:14:14.159 --> 00:14:16.213
and half of the trees are fruit trees

00:14:16.213 --> 00:14:19.223
and then half of them can be used for firewood

00:14:19.223 --> 00:14:22.275
so that the people who live on these lands are benefited from them.

00:14:22.275 --> 00:14:25.676
They take care of the trees and those trees actually really grow.

00:14:25.676 --> 00:14:34.214
And one of the things that’s really working on is… is poverty.

00:14:34.214 --> 00:14:37.958
And when I look at the world today and I see,

00:14:37.958 --> 00:14:40.748
especially in the United States,

00:14:40.748 --> 00:14:46.805
this incredible gap between people who have capital and people who don’t.

00:14:46.805 --> 00:14:53.811
And it's a very disturbing sign to me that this…

00:14:53.811 --> 00:14:55.367
the gap between rich and poor.

00:14:55.367 --> 00:14:58.541
Can you talk a little bit about how yoga would address that

00:14:58.541 --> 00:15:01.739
in terms of sustainable development?

00:15:01.739 --> 00:15:03.970
Sadhguru: See, we must understand this that

00:15:03.970 --> 00:15:08.635
we have chosen an economic model which is all about

00:15:08.635 --> 00:15:10.973
“everybody for himself or herself.”

00:15:10.973 --> 00:15:15.391
There is no larger commitment to humanity as such

00:15:15.391 --> 00:15:17.925
because that is market economy.

00:15:17.925 --> 00:15:21.930
Everybody does according to their own capabilities and skills

00:15:21.930 --> 00:15:23.413
and grab what they can grab.

00:15:23.413 --> 00:15:27.012
It's literally shoot-and-scoot economy.

00:15:27.012 --> 00:15:31.078
But we’ve gone for this, simply because

00:15:31.078 --> 00:15:36.007
the socialistic, communistic ideas have unfortunately failed.

00:15:36.007 --> 00:15:41.357
Not necessarily because they are bad because human beings are not ready for it yet,

00:15:41.357 --> 00:15:41.954
that is-

00:15:41.954 --> 00:15:45.057
poor people who had nothing, wanted to share,

00:15:45.057 --> 00:15:47.598
the rich never wanted to share.

00:15:47.598 --> 00:15:49.381
So it became a joke in the world.

00:15:49.381 --> 00:15:53.630
If the rich had to… If rich had the consciousness to share,

00:15:53.630 --> 00:15:56.422
communism would have been a great idea.

00:15:56.422 --> 00:15:58.637
But the poor want to share, rich don’t want to share.

00:15:58.637 --> 00:16:01.381
So that is the same situation here

00:16:01.381 --> 00:16:05.310
and this is the same situation building up everywhere else in the world.

00:16:05.310 --> 00:16:07.096
Is this the best way to run the world?

00:16:07.096 --> 00:16:07.946
No.

00:16:07.946 --> 00:16:09.819
But do we have a better idea? No.

00:16:09.819 --> 00:16:14.087
So (Laughs)… because right now we are in that place.

00:16:14.087 --> 00:16:17.560
So, the only thing that we can truly do is that

00:16:17.560 --> 00:16:24.018
we bring what is this… what we are referring to as yoga as a living experience.

00:16:24.018 --> 00:16:26.715
Yoga does not mean twisting your body,

00:16:26.715 --> 00:16:29.289
yoga does not mean standing on your head,

00:16:29.289 --> 00:16:31.860
yoga does not mean holding your breath.

00:16:31.860 --> 00:16:37.100
Yoga means, in some way you have transcended the limitations of your physical nature.

00:16:37.100 --> 00:16:41.525
You are beginning to experience life as a larger possibility,

00:16:41.525 --> 00:16:45.169
not just this physical form that you are.

00:16:45.169 --> 00:16:48.009
Once this becomes a living experience,

00:16:48.009 --> 00:16:52.481
sharing and living together will become a common experience everywhere.

00:16:52.481 --> 00:16:57.083
Does it mean we’re going to start communes and everybody will live together?

00:16:57.083 --> 00:16:57.841
No.

00:16:57.841 --> 00:17:00.860
We can run businesses in a more inclusive way.

00:17:00.860 --> 00:17:04.824
We can create a more inclusive economic model

00:17:04.824 --> 00:17:07.384
and this need not be done by government policy.

00:17:07.384 --> 00:17:09.931
This can be done by private individuals because

00:17:09.931 --> 00:17:13.785
there are companies which are almost as large as nations today.

00:17:13.785 --> 00:17:18.515
There are companies which budgets - which are bigger than nations.

00:17:18.515 --> 00:17:22.943
So it is very much possible that business can be run in a more inclusive way.

00:17:22.943 --> 00:17:26.360
Right now, we are thinking only of profit.

00:17:26.360 --> 00:17:30.358
Our idea of profit is very short-term kind of idea.

00:17:30.358 --> 00:17:33.116
If you really want to run your company,

00:17:33.116 --> 00:17:38.225
if you are thinking in terms of your company prospering in the next hundred, two hundred, five hundred years continuously,

00:17:38.225 --> 00:17:42.745
then it's very important that you make your customer your partner,

00:17:42.745 --> 00:17:45.807
that you make everybody else in the society your partner.

00:17:45.807 --> 00:17:49.227
Whatever you are manufacturing or whatever you’re selling

00:17:49.227 --> 00:17:50.910
or whatever the business is –

00:17:50.910 --> 00:17:54.443
whether you’re selling a safety pin or a computer or a spacecraft –

00:17:54.443 --> 00:17:58.790
essentially the business is about human well-being.

00:17:58.790 --> 00:18:00.278
If this is…

00:18:00.278 --> 00:18:04.830
this comes into the consciousness of every business person,

00:18:04.830 --> 00:18:08.311
if this comes into the consciousness of building every business

00:18:08.311 --> 00:18:10.811
that essentially this is about human well-being,

00:18:10.811 --> 00:18:13.823
we do it in so many ways but fundamentally it's about that,

00:18:13.823 --> 00:18:19.772
if this awareness and consciousness is instilled in the businesses on the planet,

00:18:19.772 --> 00:18:24.645
then you can find the capitalistic way of living need not mean disparity,

00:18:24.645 --> 00:18:27.691
can mean wellbeing to everybody.

00:18:27.691 --> 00:18:36.460
Max Kennedy: Sadhguru, I read the other day that for every dollar in government investment

00:18:36.460 --> 00:18:41.014
in developing countries that there are seven dollars now in private investment.

00:18:41.014 --> 00:18:49.449
So, how do we use yoga to yoke in the private corporations

00:18:49.449 --> 00:18:53.773
that are looking just at their bottom line to end up really having development

00:18:53.773 --> 00:18:56.365
that’s fair and just?

00:18:56.365 --> 00:19:01.900
Sadhguru: In the last twenty years I have largely focused on the business leaders because

00:19:01.900 --> 00:19:05.440
there was a time a few hundred years ago

00:19:05.440 --> 00:19:10.911
where the most influential leadership on the planet was religious leadership.

00:19:10.911 --> 00:19:14.927
Later on, when the military machines built up in a big way,

00:19:14.927 --> 00:19:17.793
the military leaders dominated the world.

00:19:17.793 --> 00:19:19.395
In the last hundred years,

00:19:19.395 --> 00:19:23.546
democratically elected leaders have become the most dominant force.

00:19:23.546 --> 00:19:25.945
In the next fifteen to twenty-five years

00:19:25.945 --> 00:19:29.638
you will see the business leaders will be the most important

00:19:29.638 --> 00:19:32.391
or influential leadership on the planet.

00:19:32.391 --> 00:19:35.664
The good thing about business is that,

00:19:35.664 --> 00:19:40.367
a businessman is willing to make a deal if the deal is good,

00:19:40.367 --> 00:19:42.399
no matter who you are.

00:19:42.399 --> 00:19:45.719
I’m saying the old prejudice of

00:19:45.719 --> 00:19:49.142
“I cannot make a deal with somebody” is going away

00:19:49.142 --> 00:19:50.995
and they’re willing to make a deal.

00:19:50.995 --> 00:19:56.442
Now, anything is sustainable only if it is beneficial to both the parties.

00:19:56.442 --> 00:20:01.397
Nothing can be sustained either in the market place or in marriage

00:20:01.397 --> 00:20:04.559
unless it’s beneficial to both the parties.

00:20:04.559 --> 00:20:07.706
Only when it’s truly beneficial to both the parties,

00:20:07.706 --> 00:20:09.294
this can be sustained.

00:20:09.294 --> 00:20:12.437
This is slowly sinking in to the business leadership.

00:20:12.437 --> 00:20:16.140
I have seen in the last twenty years prominent business leaders,

00:20:16.140 --> 00:20:20.228
their way of thinking is very, very different than what it was.

00:20:20.228 --> 00:20:24.561
My essential work has been to move individual leaders

00:20:24.561 --> 00:20:28.770
from their personal ambitions to a larger vision because

00:20:28.770 --> 00:20:33.638
a larger vision means then the business is sustainable for a long period of time.

00:20:33.638 --> 00:20:37.707
If it’s just your personal ambition the world will work against you.

00:20:37.707 --> 00:20:41.338
If you have a larger vision the world will work with you,

00:20:41.338 --> 00:20:42.823
this is the big difference.

00:20:42.823 --> 00:20:45.400
So, this is something that is slowly sinking in.

00:20:45.400 --> 00:20:46.422
You will see…

00:20:46.422 --> 00:20:51.207
If you see annual meetings of major businesses what they are talking,

00:20:51.207 --> 00:20:53.850
if you look at the Economic Forum,

00:20:53.850 --> 00:20:58.137
if you look at various economic… you know, assemblies on the planet,

00:20:58.137 --> 00:21:01.870
you will see they are all beginning to talk about a larger vision –

00:21:01.870 --> 00:21:06.138
how to make a difference rather than how to make a profit.

00:21:06.138 --> 00:21:09.392
This is become the language of the business these days.

00:21:09.392 --> 00:21:11.999
It still has to manifest in a big way

00:21:11.999 --> 00:21:17.164
but at least the language has changed from profit to making a difference.

00:21:17.164 --> 00:21:19.926
Maxwell Kennedy: Thank you. Sadhguru,

00:21:19.926 --> 00:21:23.324
When… when you look at societies all across the world

00:21:23.324 --> 00:21:27.100
there is a huge gap between what’s available to women

00:21:27.100 --> 00:21:29.156
and what’s available to men.

00:21:29.156 --> 00:21:32.997
The Sustainable Development Goals address this –

00:21:32.997 --> 00:21:39.189
how…what’s the role of gender equality in yoga?

00:21:39.189 --> 00:21:45.838
Sadhguru: See, yoga means transcending your physical nature, on one level.

00:21:45.838 --> 00:21:48.623
If you transcend your physical nature,

00:21:48.623 --> 00:21:51.998
where is the question of being a male or a female?

00:21:51.998 --> 00:21:58.403
You being a male or a female is relevant only in a few spaces in your life –

00:21:58.403 --> 00:22:01.498
in bathrooms and bedrooms,

00:22:01.498 --> 00:22:03.459
rest of the places I don’t see

00:22:03.459 --> 00:22:07.170
why you should recognize somebody as a man or a woman?

00:22:07.170 --> 00:22:11.758
Why are we identifying people with reproductory organs?

00:22:11.758 --> 00:22:16.024
If you must use a body part at least use the brain (Laughter/Applause).

00:22:23.624 --> 00:22:27.717
I think a small gender difference that is there between us

00:22:27.717 --> 00:22:32.582
to fulfill a certain aspect of our life is being stretched too far.

00:22:32.582 --> 00:22:34.998
I think this is from another period

00:22:34.998 --> 00:22:38.393
where it was not possible for a woman to participate

00:22:38.393 --> 00:22:41.598
because of variety of physical situations in the world

00:22:41.598 --> 00:22:45.382
and that is largely leveled today in most parts of the world

00:22:45.382 --> 00:22:49.890
and it’s rapidly changing everywhere I would say.

00:22:49.890 --> 00:22:54.158
I think a more active effort is needed, at least by law in most nations

00:22:54.158 --> 00:22:56.281
it is hundred percent equal,

00:22:56.281 --> 00:23:00.742
by practice there is still discrepancies

00:23:00.742 --> 00:23:02.564
which has to be worked at.

00:23:02.564 --> 00:23:05.012
I feel it’s a generational thing,

00:23:05.012 --> 00:23:07.208
once the older generation moves out,

00:23:07.208 --> 00:23:09.555
the younger generation is not looking at it that way anymore,

00:23:09.555 --> 00:23:12.318
at least I see that in all the Asian countries.

00:23:12.318 --> 00:23:16.581
It is only people beyond sixty years of age who think on…

00:23:16.581 --> 00:23:17.670
in this mode.

00:23:17.670 --> 00:23:22.369
The younger people are not thinking that way anymore.

00:23:22.369 --> 00:23:25.842
Maxwell Kennedy: Thank you. Sadhguru, I’m just gonna ask you one more question because

00:23:25.842 --> 00:23:33.252
I wanna save time for the audience who’ve been waiting to talk to you.

00:23:33.252 --> 00:23:39.672
Can you tell about how you conceive the world in thirty years?

00:23:39.672 --> 00:23:43.254
Sadhguru: What I see is for the first time,

00:23:43.254 --> 00:23:46.579
for the very first time in the history of humanity,

00:23:46.579 --> 00:23:50.673
human intellect is sparking like never before.

00:23:50.673 --> 00:23:54.894
More people on the planet today can think for themselves than ever before

00:23:54.894 --> 00:23:59.151
in the history of this human existence.

00:23:59.151 --> 00:24:03.781
So, once human intellect begins to spark like this,

00:24:03.781 --> 00:24:05.698
unless something is logically correct

00:24:05.698 --> 00:24:07.938
and scientifically verifiable,

00:24:07.938 --> 00:24:10.405
it will fail in future.

00:24:10.405 --> 00:24:13.395
You may be willing to listen to a few things

00:24:13.395 --> 00:24:15.866
but your children are not going to listen to anything

00:24:15.866 --> 00:24:17.872
that does not make sense to them.

00:24:17.872 --> 00:24:21.563
It does not matter from what authority it comes from.

00:24:21.563 --> 00:24:23.357
Or in other words,

00:24:23.357 --> 00:24:26.157
we are moving into a era

00:24:26.157 --> 00:24:30.712
where authority cannot be the truth,

00:24:30.712 --> 00:24:33.752
truth will be the only authority in future.

00:24:33.752 --> 00:24:35.417
We are getting there because

00:24:35.417 --> 00:24:38.215
everybody is beginning to ask questions

00:24:38.215 --> 00:24:41.502
and people are not afraid to ask questions anymore.

00:24:41.502 --> 00:24:43.336
So, this is bound to happen.

00:24:43.336 --> 00:24:44.832
Once this happens,

00:24:44.832 --> 00:24:51.292
human aspiration for well-being has to have a logically correct

00:24:51.292 --> 00:24:54.297
and scientifically ascertainable methodology.

00:24:54.297 --> 00:24:59.162
And it’s of tremendous importance that today

00:24:59.162 --> 00:25:05.005
the International Yoga Day has been declared in the last one year.

00:25:05.005 --> 00:25:07.813
It was mooted by the Prime Minister

00:25:07.813 --> 00:25:10.619
but it was almost like the world was waiting for it

00:25:10.619 --> 00:25:13.499
as they mentioned hundred-and-seventy-seven countries,

00:25:13.499 --> 00:25:16.492
never before in the history of United Nations,

00:25:16.492 --> 00:25:20.063
all of them agreed upon one thing as they agreed upon yoga.

00:25:20.063 --> 00:25:22.477
It looked like they were waiting for it.

00:25:22.477 --> 00:25:25.486
Yes, the world has been waiting for a scientific

00:25:25.486 --> 00:25:30.241
and a logically correct solution for human well-being.

00:25:30.241 --> 00:25:33.788
The aspiration for human well-being will not stop.

00:25:33.788 --> 00:25:39.993
Unless we provide a proper, scientifically structured methodology

00:25:39.993 --> 00:25:45.455
then people in terms of well-being will move towards chemicals.

00:25:45.455 --> 00:25:48.732
This is a deep… a grave concern in the world,

00:25:48.732 --> 00:25:53.617
the number of people moving towards alcohol and drugs in the last twenty-five years

00:25:53.617 --> 00:25:59.353
must be… maybe five hundred to thousand percent more than what it was twenty-five years ago.

00:25:59.353 --> 00:26:01.821
This is mainly because

00:26:01.821 --> 00:26:04.174
in pursuit of human well-being

00:26:04.174 --> 00:26:08.567
there are no logically correct answers to their questions.

00:26:08.567 --> 00:26:12.580
That is the reason why human beings are seeking these kind of solutions.

00:26:12.580 --> 00:26:16.387
Unless we provide this, this is a natural progression.

00:26:16.387 --> 00:26:22.191
I see in the next thirty years to fifty years there will be a big movement towards

00:26:22.191 --> 00:26:25.785
a scientific process for inner well-being

00:26:25.785 --> 00:26:30.680
and this is a right time to be here at this forum

00:26:30.680 --> 00:26:34.327
and this yoga becoming a worldwide thing.

00:26:34.327 --> 00:26:37.858
We must understand yoga is not an Indian thing.

00:26:37.858 --> 00:26:43.788
If you want to call yoga Indian then you must call gravity European, okay

00:26:43.788 --> 00:26:45.555
(Laughter/Applause)

00:26:50.805 --> 00:26:55.992
Because… Yes, it… it originated from that place

00:26:55.992 --> 00:26:58.619
because India is one place where

00:26:58.619 --> 00:27:05.253
for a few millennia we had uninterrupted time to look deep inwards

00:27:05.253 --> 00:27:09.388
and to look at the human mechanism in utmost profoundness

00:27:09.388 --> 00:27:11.416
as to how this (Referring to oneself) functions,

00:27:11.416 --> 00:27:14.565
what is the ultimate possibility within this human mechanism.

00:27:14.565 --> 00:27:19.935
This has taken a few millennia to understand and arrive at this possibility.

00:27:19.935 --> 00:27:23.220
And yoga… I want this message to go –

00:27:23.220 --> 00:27:27.531
“The science of yoga is not just about health,

00:27:27.531 --> 00:27:30.004
it’s not just about fitness,

00:27:30.004 --> 00:27:34.415
it is an ultimate solution for every aspect of human existence.”

00:27:34.415 --> 00:27:36.578
There is different types of yogas.

00:27:36.578 --> 00:27:39.256
Yoga can be taught in different dimensions -

00:27:39.256 --> 00:27:44.555
the ultimate possibility of raising beyond our physical nature,

00:27:44.555 --> 00:27:49.695
the ultimate possibility of knowing life in its fullest way.

00:27:49.695 --> 00:27:52.040
The word yoga means union.

00:27:52.040 --> 00:27:56.060
The word yogi means one who has experienced this union.

00:27:56.060 --> 00:28:00.645
We need not one, two, five yogis, we need millions of them,

00:28:00.645 --> 00:28:04.098
who have a sense of union with the rest of the universe,

00:28:04.098 --> 00:28:08.328
particularly those who hold responsible positions in the world.

00:28:08.328 --> 00:28:10.899
They must come to this experience

00:28:10.899 --> 00:28:17.218
because leadership essentially means you have the privilege of touching other people’s lives.

00:28:17.218 --> 00:28:25.888
What you think, what you feel and what you do, every single thought, emotion and action either makes or breaks people’s lives,

00:28:25.888 --> 00:28:27.680
that’s what leadership means.

00:28:27.680 --> 00:28:31.420
When you are given such a privilege it’s very, very important

00:28:31.420 --> 00:28:36.995
that you are in a state of yoga that you experience life around you as yourself.

00:28:36.995 --> 00:28:42.110
If we… If any of us feel the work that we’re doing is important,

00:28:42.110 --> 00:28:46.550
the first and foremost thing is we must work upon ourselves (Applause).

00:41:56.491 --> 00:41:59.831
Permanent representative of Nepal: I come from Nepal, from the Eastern hills of Nepal,

00:41:59.831 --> 00:42:03.385
a place… an environment which is extremely conducive for yoga.

00:42:03.385 --> 00:42:08.611
And I also come from a family and community practicing yoga.

00:42:08.611 --> 00:42:12.508
But then I’m always worried about this question of accessibility.

00:42:12.508 --> 00:42:17.225
It has to do with the commercialization of yoga today.

00:42:17.225 --> 00:42:23.212
The commercialization and hundreds and thousands of different types of yoga

00:42:23.212 --> 00:42:26.905
getting into the heads of young minds

00:42:26.905 --> 00:42:29.342
and different ages of people

00:42:29.342 --> 00:42:35.458
mostly also in terms of fashion… in the forms of fashion,

00:42:35.458 --> 00:42:40.892
what would be your wise guidance to us

00:42:40.892 --> 00:42:44.588
to deal with the perhaps unnecessary

00:42:44.588 --> 00:42:49.254
or over commercialization of yoga.

00:42:49.254 --> 00:42:53.234
Sadhguru: Whatever becomes reasonably popular,

00:42:53.234 --> 00:42:56.596
there’ll be enterprise around that.

00:42:56.596 --> 00:43:00.606
You shouldn’t be surprised when you step out on the Times Square,

00:43:00.606 --> 00:43:07.407
people will be selling yoga T-shirts and yoga whatever, whatever, okay (Laughs)?

00:43:07.407 --> 00:43:10.879
We shouldn’t be distracted or disturbed by these things.

00:43:10.879 --> 00:43:16.609
This is a part of a social thing - it happens.

00:43:16.609 --> 00:43:18.070
At the same time,

00:43:18.070 --> 00:43:20.873
the core of yoga is not disturbed in any way.

00:43:20.873 --> 00:43:24.833
On the surface there are small distortions here and there.

00:43:24.833 --> 00:43:27.972
I would say, for the larger public to start with…

00:43:27.972 --> 00:43:29.643
Like, this year,

00:43:29.643 --> 00:43:31.590
when you know, about four months ago,

00:43:31.590 --> 00:43:38.530
when I came to know that over 9000 children below eighteen years of age committed suicide in India

00:43:38.530 --> 00:43:42.892
and over 1700 below thirteen years of age committed suicide,

00:43:42.892 --> 00:43:46.204
it… I just thought

00:43:46.204 --> 00:43:52.305
if our children start committing suicide we are doing something fundamentally wrong.

00:43:52.305 --> 00:43:54.741
A child is a fresh life.

00:43:54.741 --> 00:43:57.296
A child is an exuberant life.

00:43:57.296 --> 00:43:59.913
A child should be a bundle of joy

00:43:59.913 --> 00:44:03.912
but instead of that they’re deciding to take their own life

00:44:03.912 --> 00:44:06.028
which is deeply disturbing.

00:44:06.028 --> 00:44:09.406
This is not a statement about the child who took his life

00:44:09.406 --> 00:44:11.448
but this is a statement about all of us –

00:44:11.448 --> 00:44:14.082
what are we doing with our societies?

00:44:14.082 --> 00:44:18.159
So, off the cuff I said let's touch 10,000 schools.

00:44:18.159 --> 00:44:22.118
But today, with the cooperation of various state governments

00:44:22.118 --> 00:44:24.525
we are touching nearly 30,000 schools,

00:44:24.525 --> 00:44:26.390
over 20 million children.

00:44:26.390 --> 00:44:28.236
Why I’m saying this is,

00:44:28.236 --> 00:44:30.112
why this has become possible is

00:44:30.112 --> 00:44:33.791
because we are offering what is called as Upa-Yoga.

00:44:33.791 --> 00:44:37.311
Upa-Yoga means pre-yoga or sub-yoga.

00:44:37.311 --> 00:44:40.493
Why this effort towards Upa-Yoga is,

00:44:40.493 --> 00:44:42.511
if you offer yoga,

00:44:42.511 --> 00:44:46.069
however innocuous the practice may look to start with,

00:44:46.069 --> 00:44:48.549
it has a spiritual dimension to it.

00:44:48.549 --> 00:44:52.874
Transmitting spiritual dimension to an unconscious population,

00:44:52.874 --> 00:44:54.405
who are not ready for it

00:44:54.405 --> 00:44:58.732
and without a certain level of expertise in the teachers

00:44:58.732 --> 00:45:02.054
could be irresponsible over a period of time.

00:45:02.054 --> 00:45:07.499
So, we are teaching Upa-Yoga which has mainly physiological and psychological benefits

00:45:07.499 --> 00:45:10.110
and here you can't do anything wrong.

00:45:10.110 --> 00:45:11.075
It's on the video.

00:45:11.075 --> 00:45:15.441
All the teacher has to do is make corrections and make sure people are not doing it wrong.

00:45:15.441 --> 00:45:20.692
I think it's a good way to spread yoga in the world is through Upa-Yoga.

00:45:20.692 --> 00:45:26.643
Upa-Yoga… the word Upa-Yog in Indian languages today has acquired the meaning of being useful,

00:45:26.643 --> 00:45:30.699
but actually its originates from this that it's a pre-yoga or sub-yoga

00:45:30.699 --> 00:45:33.909
or a start-up… start-up yoga it is.

00:45:33.909 --> 00:45:38.324
And it's best to start that way with large populations because

00:45:38.324 --> 00:45:42.163
when you start off an unconscious spiritual process for people,

00:45:42.163 --> 00:45:44.739
many of them may not be ready for it,

00:45:44.739 --> 00:45:46.302
even if it's a good thing.

00:45:46.302 --> 00:45:48.937
Even if good thing happens to you when you’re not ready for it,

00:45:48.937 --> 00:45:51.705
thing’s may (Laughs) not work very well.

00:45:51.705 --> 00:45:57.421
So, Upa-Yoga is a… a very distinct way and a safe way

00:45:57.421 --> 00:46:00.156
to take yoga to the world large scale.

00:46:00.156 --> 00:46:02.147
After this happens,

00:46:02.147 --> 00:46:03.918
once they feel the benefits,

00:46:03.918 --> 00:46:05.948
once they experience what difference it makes,

00:46:05.948 --> 00:46:10.176
they will naturally seek yoga in a more serious manner

00:46:10.176 --> 00:46:13.031
and that is when yoga should come into their lives.

00:46:13.031 --> 00:46:16.006
This could solve the concern that you expressed.

00:46:16.006 --> 00:46:17.631
But at the same time,

00:46:17.631 --> 00:46:20.534
somebody is doing something funny in the name of yoga,

00:46:20.534 --> 00:46:24.445
it doesn’t concern me because those things will always happen.

00:46:24.445 --> 00:46:29.269
But it’s good that even commercial establishments are talking yoga.

00:46:29.269 --> 00:46:32.330
This means it's really on (Laughter/Applause).

00:46:34.460 --> 00:46:37.577
Speaker: I will now call upon Mister Herman Bravo

00:46:37.577 --> 00:46:41.002
who is the President of the Yoga Club right here at the UN.

00:46:41.002 --> 00:46:43.171
Mister Bravo you have the floor.

00:48:55.583 --> 00:49:00.552
Nata Menabde: I have spent five years of my life in India before coming here in New York.

00:49:00.552 --> 00:49:07.608
And of course, for me it’s something very special to be here today at this day.

00:49:07.608 --> 00:49:22.015
And it’s special because I… You mentioned Sadhguru, that we cannot call or compare and say that yoga is Indian.

00:49:22.015 --> 00:49:28.797
But, it comes from India. And indeed it is India’s gift to the human kind to all over the world.

00:49:28.797 --> 00:49:40.210
And it is very special because of that. And I could see the impact of yoga practice on communities in India,

00:49:40.210 --> 00:49:46.944
so it makes a difference. And this is why, this is such a great gift of civilization.

00:49:46.944 --> 00:49:59.354
The whole country in India, every quarter of it breathes essence of yoga. And it is the civilization calm of yoga that has moved me when I was there.

00:49:59.354 --> 00:50:07.703
In my work, we are dealing with health issues. It is no news now that yoga is very good for health.

00:50:07.703 --> 00:50:16.954
But we also know now that health is no longer stand alone
one of the Sustainable Development Goals.

00:50:16.954 --> 00:50:29.137
It is actually determinant for any other goal to be achieved.
Therefore yoga has a very different meaning and different, indeed, interconnecting nature

00:50:29.137 --> 00:50:37.472
because it does help people to feel better, live better, breathe better, act better, unite better,

00:50:37.472 --> 00:50:47.489
come into interconnectedness which is indeed essential for sustaining our planet and connects planet to the people.

00:50:47.489 --> 00:50:56.690
So therefore, of course, we know today, proven through many clinical trials that yoga helps in many conditions –

00:50:56.690 --> 00:51:00.650
mental health conditions, depression, heart conditions,many other conditions, joint and so on. So this is not new.

00:51:00.650 --> 00:51:15.039
But there has been traditional resistance to integrate yoga practice and other perhaps traditional medicine practices

00:51:15.039 --> 00:51:24.461
which are of course available world-wide but known also in India, to integrate them to the allopathic medicine.

00:51:24.461 --> 00:51:28.927
And this resistance is slowly being overcome

00:51:28.927 --> 00:51:36.703
We as WHO are trying to put our support into this process.

00:51:36.703 --> 00:51:39.477
Recently, this year in May,

00:51:39.477 --> 00:51:41.880
in fact India has signed an…

00:51:41.880 --> 00:51:46.521
I would say, landmark agreement with the World Health Organization to promote

00:51:46.521 --> 00:51:52.121
traditional medicine, yoga included and to ensure quality and safety

00:51:52.121 --> 00:51:54.435
of these traditional practices.

00:51:54.435 --> 00:52:00.087
But more so, to integrate these practices into our health services,

00:52:00.087 --> 00:52:01.817
primary health care

00:52:01.817 --> 00:52:04.683
and all other services that we know.

00:52:04.683 --> 00:52:07.290
So, it is now deeply understood that,

00:52:07.290 --> 00:52:13.095
as all of human beings need some or another kind of health services -

00:52:13.095 --> 00:52:14.705
be it vaccination,

00:52:14.705 --> 00:52:16.825
if they are very healthy

00:52:16.825 --> 00:52:20.501
or any other more serious services.

00:52:20.501 --> 00:52:25.793
They also need to practice yoga because it prevents many illnesses,

00:52:25.793 --> 00:52:28.094
it also gives peace of mind.

00:52:28.094 --> 00:52:33.264
It teaches us how to cope with all those different things

00:52:33.264 --> 00:52:35.634
that modern life,

00:52:35.634 --> 00:52:38.454
stress puts on human brain.

00:52:38.454 --> 00:52:41.904
And therefore, we to stand forward

00:52:41.904 --> 00:52:48.614
and we want to support promotion and inclusion of yoga into medical practice

00:52:48.614 --> 00:52:50.240
all over the world.

00:52:50.240 --> 00:52:53.012
We will collaborate with India on that.

00:52:53.012 --> 00:52:55.678
But my question to you would be

00:52:55.678 --> 00:53:00.055
is there any good secret beyond of what you have said,

00:53:00.055 --> 00:53:04.995
how we can bring this different dimensions of health together,

00:53:04.995 --> 00:53:07.076
integrate them in a better way

00:53:07.076 --> 00:53:11.892
and make sure that yoga is no longer seen as something separate

00:53:11.892 --> 00:53:16.761
from what we do in health services traditionally?

00:53:16.761 --> 00:53:17.818
Thank you.

00:53:17.818 --> 00:53:21.038
Thank you very much for being here today (Applause).

00:53:26.558 --> 00:53:31.014
Sadhguru: When our commitment has to shift to health,

00:53:31.014 --> 00:53:33.087
not to a particular system.

00:53:33.087 --> 00:53:36.946
People are married to a particular system most of the time

00:53:36.946 --> 00:53:40.944
and they defend that system at any cost, no matter what.

00:53:40.944 --> 00:53:44.136
Every system in the world has something to contribute

00:53:44.136 --> 00:53:48.396
but instead of being committed to health we are committed to those systems.

00:53:48.396 --> 00:53:54.109
Because of this, there has been a lot of dislocation in how health can come about.

00:53:54.109 --> 00:53:56.373
So, in Southern India,

00:53:56.373 --> 00:53:58.950
in the rural part of Tamil Nadu

00:53:58.950 --> 00:54:02.091
we brought this about -

00:54:02.091 --> 00:54:04.238
these five dimensions,

00:54:04.238 --> 00:54:13.100
Allopathy, Siddha, Ayurveda, Unani and Yoga together practice along with naturopathy way of doing things.

00:54:13.100 --> 00:54:16.713
It has done miraculous things to the populations.

00:54:16.713 --> 00:54:20.919
We were the first pilot project by the Ayush project

00:54:20.919 --> 00:54:22.840
when it started ten years ago.

00:54:22.840 --> 00:54:25.189
Now Ayush has become a Ministry.

00:54:25.189 --> 00:54:28.881
I think yesterday or in the last week they have declared a Ayush University

00:54:28.881 --> 00:54:33.137
which means Ayurveda, Yoga, Siddha and all these things put together.

00:54:33.137 --> 00:54:36.147
This we started almost fifteen years ago

00:54:36.147 --> 00:54:38.507
and today it is an active part.

00:54:38.507 --> 00:54:39.851
What we have done is,

00:54:39.851 --> 00:54:43.038
we have medical vans which go with a…

00:54:43.038 --> 00:54:47.924
an allopathic doctor and a Siddha doctor plus we have created

00:54:47.924 --> 00:54:56.689
over one-hundred-and-twelve or thirteen village gardens

00:54:56.689 --> 00:54:58.798
where we grow herbs

00:54:58.798 --> 00:55:01.491
over hundred… hundred and odd different types of herbs

00:55:01.491 --> 00:55:03.321
in a common piece of land

00:55:03.321 --> 00:55:06.500
where people are taught how to make use of it.

00:55:06.500 --> 00:55:08.217
For small things like stomach ache,

00:55:08.217 --> 00:55:08.908
headache,

00:55:08.908 --> 00:55:10.160
fever for the children,

00:55:10.160 --> 00:55:12.209
diarrhea, these kind of things

00:55:12.209 --> 00:55:14.963
all our grandmothers knew how to treat this.

00:55:14.963 --> 00:55:18.761
Unfortunately, even for these, people are going to the doctors today.

00:55:18.761 --> 00:55:23.258
And the way it is being treated with elaborate medication.

00:55:23.258 --> 00:55:25.697
Generally, in rural India

00:55:25.697 --> 00:55:28.296
the cost of the medicine,

00:55:28.296 --> 00:55:33.287
if you fall sick for fifteen days it takes a year for you to recover, with…

00:55:33.287 --> 00:55:37.614
The economics of the family gets hit for almost a year.

00:55:37.614 --> 00:55:39.947
If fifteen days somebody is down

00:55:39.947 --> 00:55:44.319
and they visit the doctor, and the volume of medication and treatment that happens,

00:55:44.319 --> 00:55:47.901
kind of economically sets them back quite a bit.

00:55:47.901 --> 00:55:49.392
So, we have…

00:55:49.392 --> 00:55:51.515
our commitment is to health,

00:55:51.515 --> 00:55:53.530
not to a particular system.

00:55:53.530 --> 00:55:58.033
And right now the government of India is doing serious efforts to integrate this thing

00:55:58.033 --> 00:56:01.833
and we’ve been doing this for over fifteen years very effectively.

00:56:01.833 --> 00:56:05.901
I must tell you a simple thing in rural India which can be… I was…

00:56:05.901 --> 00:56:07.783
Just last one week I was in Africa.

00:56:07.783 --> 00:56:11.241
Even there I thought this is something that’ll work.

00:56:11.241 --> 00:56:13.456
We created what is called as a Wave of Health.

00:56:13.456 --> 00:56:15.820
About simple things -

00:56:15.820 --> 00:56:19.628
how health can be created with… within the family,

00:56:19.628 --> 00:56:20.630
for every family.

00:56:20.630 --> 00:56:22.401
One of the things that was done -

00:56:22.401 --> 00:56:23.703
I won't go into all the details -

00:56:23.703 --> 00:56:25.083
one simple thing we did was,

00:56:25.083 --> 00:56:32.137
every home should have a Papaya tree, a banana tree, a Murungu tree and a patch of greens.

00:56:32.137 --> 00:56:37.134
This transformed health situations in such a big way.

00:56:37.134 --> 00:56:39.446
You won't believe, such a small initiative,

00:56:39.446 --> 00:56:43.201
such a simple initiative, what a difference it has done to peoples’ lives.

00:56:43.201 --> 00:56:48.939
Like this, small initiatives can be brought because considering the economics of those families,

00:56:48.939 --> 00:56:53.511
it's very important we need to come up with solutions that works for them.

00:56:53.511 --> 00:56:57.636
In this, yoga practice has a significant role because

00:56:57.636 --> 00:57:05.621
creating a vibrant… healthy, vibrant and effervescent population is very, very important

00:57:05.621 --> 00:57:07.921
to fulfill these sustainable goals.

00:57:07.921 --> 00:57:10.289
If we don’t create that kind of population

00:57:10.289 --> 00:57:13.674
we will be only talking about sustainability,

00:57:13.674 --> 00:57:14.753
it will not happen.

00:57:14.753 --> 00:57:16.212
We need to create this.

00:57:16.212 --> 00:57:22.394
And the goal is the tools of self-transformation should not be in the hands of a guru

00:57:22.394 --> 00:57:24.571
or an organization

00:57:24.571 --> 00:57:26.004
or some other authority.

00:57:26.004 --> 00:57:29.016
The idea is to bring this into everybody’s life.

00:57:29.016 --> 00:57:33.308
Like today, everybody owns a toothbrush which has created oral health,

00:57:33.308 --> 00:57:34.332
just like that

00:57:34.332 --> 00:57:38.640
everybody should have some tools for self-transformation.

00:57:38.640 --> 00:57:42.041
It is with this kind of commitment that we are going ahead

00:57:42.041 --> 00:57:44.792
and there is a big support now in the world.

00:57:44.792 --> 00:57:45.657
Wherever we go -

00:57:45.657 --> 00:57:49.963
in the remotest parts of Africa that I was there in the last one week,

00:57:49.963 --> 00:57:54.092
it was incredible to see that all of them know about yoga.

00:57:54.092 --> 00:57:57.595
I know this twenty-five years ago when I went into rural India,

00:57:57.595 --> 00:57:59.322
in a big way,

00:57:59.322 --> 00:58:02.033
they knew what is coco-cola

00:58:02.033 --> 00:58:03.664
but they did not know what is yoga (Laughter).

00:58:03.664 --> 00:58:08.752
But today, in the remotest part of Africa people know what is yoga.

00:58:08.752 --> 00:58:11.774
This is transformation in many ways (Applause).

00:59:20.925 --> 00:59:26.550
Speaker: I now give the floor to Mister Rajiv Lalla who has joined us all the way from Texas.

00:59:26.550 --> 00:59:31.176
Rajiv Lalla: If you could help us understand the role of Sadhguru, of a teacher,

00:59:31.176 --> 00:59:38.242
not in the true academic sense where a STEM professor teaches me science and technology,

00:59:38.242 --> 00:59:45.163
but rather coming from humanity and that union among all of us.

00:59:45.163 --> 00:59:47.827
Sadhguru: (Laughs) When you say a Sadhguru,

00:59:47.827 --> 00:59:53.387
you’re saying an uneducated guru, that’s what it means.

00:59:53.387 --> 00:59:57.917
Because you don’t go… come to a Sadhguru to know about the scriptures,

00:59:57.917 --> 01:00:01.290
you don’t come to Sadhguru to know about rituals

01:00:01.290 --> 01:00:05.735
because the only thing that I know is I know this piece of life (Referring to oneself)

01:00:05.735 --> 01:00:08.516
from its origin to its ultimate and this’s all I know.

01:00:08.516 --> 01:00:09.839
By knowing this,

01:00:09.839 --> 01:00:14.458
by inference you know just about everything because

01:00:14.458 --> 01:00:16.361
everything is made the same way.

01:00:16.361 --> 01:00:20.412
Today, there is something called as a Constructional Theory

01:00:20.412 --> 01:00:23.602
where they’re talking about how the atom and the cosmos are essentially,

01:00:23.602 --> 01:00:25.883
fundamentally same design,

01:00:25.883 --> 01:00:29.739
only the sophistication and complexity is multiplying.

01:00:29.739 --> 01:00:32.259
So, the amoeba and you and me are made the same way,

01:00:32.259 --> 01:00:35.061
only the complexity has multiplied.

01:00:35.061 --> 01:00:36.363
Having said that,

01:00:36.363 --> 01:00:40.257
in what way is a guru relevant means -

01:00:40.257 --> 01:00:46.118
you’re trying to walk an unchartered terrain.

01:00:46.118 --> 01:00:51.934
Every year, I trek in the Himalayas in Nepal and Tibet.

01:00:51.934 --> 01:00:55.390
Once you go into the mountains,

01:00:55.390 --> 01:00:58.718
that illiterate Sherpa who is there,

01:00:58.718 --> 01:01:04.249
who has not been to school but if he says “right” you turn right,

01:01:04.249 --> 01:01:06.262
if he says “left” you turn left.

01:01:06.262 --> 01:01:10.347
You better do that otherwise you won't come back (Laughs).

01:01:10.347 --> 01:01:12.857
You do that because he knows the terrain.

01:01:12.857 --> 01:01:15.006
The same goes for this.

01:01:15.006 --> 01:01:18.138
This is just an inner terrain.

01:01:18.138 --> 01:01:22.031
It's best to walk with somebody who’s already walked the path,

01:01:22.031 --> 01:01:25.207
otherwise simple things will become complicated.

01:01:25.207 --> 01:01:28.415
What is next door, you will go around the world

01:01:28.415 --> 01:01:30.011
and come back to it.

01:01:30.011 --> 01:01:31.545
All this complication about…

01:01:31.545 --> 01:01:34.572
For example, today if you utter the word meditation,

01:01:34.572 --> 01:01:37.601
people think something very difficult to do.

01:01:37.601 --> 01:01:39.413
To put it simply,

01:01:39.413 --> 01:01:41.983
first of all the word meditation,

01:01:41.983 --> 01:01:45.472
English word meditation does not describe anything in particular.

01:01:45.472 --> 01:01:49.061
If you sit with your eyes closed they’re saying (Laughs)

01:01:49.061 --> 01:01:49.871
you’re meditating.

01:01:49.871 --> 01:01:54.738
With your eyes closed you can do japa, tapa, dharana, dhyana, samadhi, shoonya,

01:01:54.738 --> 01:01:56.882
there are any number of things you could do

01:01:56.882 --> 01:02:00.880
or you might have just mastered the art of sleeping in vertical postures

01:02:00.880 --> 01:02:01.803
(Laughter).

01:02:01.803 --> 01:02:03.605
It happens (Laughs).

01:02:03.605 --> 01:02:08.805
So, when we say meditation, we must understand, it's not an act,

01:02:08.805 --> 01:02:10.755
it is a quality.

01:02:10.755 --> 01:02:13.365
It is like you want flowers in your garden,

01:02:13.365 --> 01:02:19.259
if you want flowers in your garden you don’t have to sit there and do flower meditation.

01:02:19.259 --> 01:02:21.457
You don’t have to think flowers.

01:02:21.457 --> 01:02:25.686
You have to think soil, manure, water, sunlight -

01:02:25.686 --> 01:02:27.639
have nothing to do with flowers

01:02:27.639 --> 01:02:30.665
but if you do those things flowers will happen

01:02:30.665 --> 01:02:32.693
because it's a consequence.

01:02:32.693 --> 01:02:38.053
Right now, because we have gotten into this madness of being a goal-oriented society,

01:02:38.053 --> 01:02:40.107
we are interested in the flower,

01:02:40.107 --> 01:02:42.240
we are not interested in the plant.

01:02:42.240 --> 01:02:46.516
This is the fundamental that the yoga will change within you.

01:02:46.516 --> 01:02:50.350
You understand that you have to handle the process right

01:02:50.350 --> 01:02:52.627
for a consequence to happen.

01:02:52.627 --> 01:02:54.686
So, in yoga there is a saying that

01:02:54.686 --> 01:02:58.493
if you’re goal oriented, your one eye will be on the goal,

01:02:58.493 --> 01:03:01.315
that means you will find your way only with one eye,

01:03:01.315 --> 01:03:03.897
which is an inefficient way of doing things.

01:03:03.897 --> 01:03:06.272
If you use both your eyes to find your way,

01:03:06.272 --> 01:03:07.849
it's much more efficient.

01:03:07.849 --> 01:03:10.179
So, why is a guru needed?

01:03:10.179 --> 01:03:12.581
It can be done without it.

01:03:12.581 --> 01:03:15.891
I… I’m asking you a simple question –

01:03:15.891 --> 01:03:18.369
even to learn ABC, the alphabet,

01:03:18.369 --> 01:03:20.225
you needed a teacher.

01:03:20.225 --> 01:03:22.487
But you could have learnt it by yourself,

01:03:22.487 --> 01:03:24.414
maybe you would have taken a lifetime,

01:03:24.414 --> 01:03:27.871
but the teacher taught it to you in a month or two, that’s a big difference.

01:03:27.871 --> 01:03:32.424
So, like somebody was talking to me and they asked what is this Guru about.

01:03:32.424 --> 01:03:36.678
I said, this is the GPS, a living GPS -

01:03:36.678 --> 01:03:41.025
a Guru Positioning System, you know (Few Laughs)!

01:03:41.025 --> 01:03:43.422
If you want to find your way,

01:03:43.422 --> 01:03:45.925
it’s best… in unchartered terrain,

01:03:45.925 --> 01:03:47.466
unknown terrain,

01:03:47.466 --> 01:03:53.723
it’s best to walk with somebody who has already done the terrain once or many times,

01:03:53.723 --> 01:03:59.150
otherwise simple things will become very complex (Applause).

01:04:36.050 --> 01:04:39.281
Denise Couture: How do you see the UN system,

01:04:39.281 --> 01:04:42.593
meaning the secretarial staff who work here,

01:04:42.593 --> 01:04:45.398
the diplomats from the different countries,

01:04:45.398 --> 01:04:48.090
business and the NGOs,

01:04:48.090 --> 01:04:51.481
civil society who try to implement the SDGs,

01:04:51.481 --> 01:04:54.585
how do you see yoga bringing us all together.

01:04:54.585 --> 01:04:57.485
Thank you so much (Applause).

01:04:59.915 --> 01:05:04.047
Sadhguru: This is being said again and again about peace.

01:05:04.047 --> 01:05:07.298
See, we need to look at this.

01:05:07.298 --> 01:05:11.619
When we say peace or mental peace as people are talking about it,

01:05:11.619 --> 01:05:18.457
today even so-called spiritual leaders are talking about peace being the highest goal in one’s life.

01:05:18.457 --> 01:05:20.591
But I would like to ask you,

01:05:20.591 --> 01:05:22.861
please look at your life and see,

01:05:22.861 --> 01:05:24.931
if you want to enjoy your dinner tonight,

01:05:24.931 --> 01:05:30.728
even if you are not ecstatic at least you must be peaceful to enjoy your dinner.

01:05:30.728 --> 01:05:33.386
If you want to enjoy the people around you

01:05:33.386 --> 01:05:35.409
at least you must be peaceful and happy.

01:05:35.409 --> 01:05:38.108
If you want to enjoy your walk on the street you must be peaceful and happy

01:05:38.108 --> 01:05:40.045
otherwise this is not possible.

01:05:40.045 --> 01:05:44.259
So, what is very fundamental to… A fundamental requirement in our life,

01:05:44.259 --> 01:05:47.892
unfortunately we are pushing it as an ultimate goal of our life.

01:05:47.892 --> 01:05:50.629
To be peaceful is not the highest thing,

01:05:50.629 --> 01:05:52.803
it is the most basic requirement.

01:05:52.803 --> 01:05:55.261
If a human being cannot even be peaceful

01:05:55.261 --> 01:05:57.409
there is really nothing that they can do.

01:05:57.409 --> 01:06:02.969
This means that you are not even able to harness your body and mind

01:06:02.969 --> 01:06:07.177
the way you should.

01:06:07.177 --> 01:06:09.880
To look at it from one perspective,

01:06:09.880 --> 01:06:12.941
all human experience has a chemical basis to it.

01:06:12.941 --> 01:06:15.600
What you call as peace is a certain kind of chemistry,

01:06:15.600 --> 01:06:17.994
what you call as joy is another kind of chemistry,

01:06:17.994 --> 01:06:19.595
blissfulness another,

01:06:19.595 --> 01:06:20.902
ecstasy another,

01:06:20.902 --> 01:06:26.168
agony another kind, anxiety, fear, stress, tension whatever you call it.

01:06:26.168 --> 01:06:29.694
Every human experience has a chemical basis to it.

01:06:29.694 --> 01:06:33.292
We have not been thought about how to deal with this (Referring to oneself).

01:06:33.292 --> 01:06:36.598
When I say how to deal with this – as is…

01:06:36.598 --> 01:06:39.866
as a technology if you want to look at this (Referring to oneself) as a machine,

01:06:39.866 --> 01:06:44.057
this is the most sophisticated piece of technology on the planet.

01:06:44.057 --> 01:06:49.208
The question is to deal with this high level of technology

01:06:49.208 --> 01:06:52.177
have you read even the user’s manual,

01:06:52.177 --> 01:06:53.412
that’s a question?

01:06:53.412 --> 01:06:57.061
Yoga means it is the user’s manual of

01:06:57.061 --> 01:06:58.819
how to conduct this one (Referring to oneself).

01:06:58.819 --> 01:07:04.124
I would say when you ask this question – how to bring all these diverse people together in this organization,

01:07:04.124 --> 01:07:07.206
it’s best to start with the simplest process

01:07:07.206 --> 01:07:12.122
which does not even need a specific allotment of time.

01:07:12.122 --> 01:07:14.514
This is where Upa-Yoga will become useful.

01:07:14.514 --> 01:07:19.521
People can sit in their work spaces and right there they can do it,

01:07:19.521 --> 01:07:20.425
three minutes,

01:07:20.425 --> 01:07:22.239
anytime they feel like it.

01:07:22.239 --> 01:07:24.341
It does not need a specific condition,

01:07:24.341 --> 01:07:26.776
it does not need a specific time,

01:07:26.776 --> 01:07:29.690
if they see the benefit which they definitely will,

01:07:29.690 --> 01:07:35.109
in a matter of two weeks’ time they will see a distinct benefit doing it wherever they are.

01:07:35.109 --> 01:07:41.064
It does not need any kind of specific discipline or time or other conditions required

01:07:41.064 --> 01:07:43.888
for normal… the proper yoga to be done.

01:07:43.888 --> 01:07:47.477
I think this would be a good way to integrate them because

01:07:47.477 --> 01:07:50.128
this predates all religion.

01:07:50.128 --> 01:07:52.546
This is not about you versus me.

01:07:52.546 --> 01:07:56.423
This is why I said this is not Indian because

01:07:56.423 --> 01:07:58.420
a science cannot be Indian. Yes,

01:07:58.420 --> 01:08:00.226
it originated from India,

01:08:00.226 --> 01:08:04.426
as Indians we are proud of it but it does not belong to India.

01:08:04.426 --> 01:08:09.496
The very fact that United Nations has declared an International Yoga Day means

01:08:09.496 --> 01:08:12.505
India has gifted it to the world.

01:08:12.505 --> 01:08:14.433
It does not belong to India anymore.

01:08:14.433 --> 01:08:18.860
We (Applause)…

01:08:18.860 --> 01:08:22.321
It’s… It’s not something that we have to possess and identify with.

01:08:22.321 --> 01:08:26.950
The significant aspect of my personal work has been

01:08:26.950 --> 01:08:31.719
to remove all the frills of culture that yoga had acquired

01:08:31.719 --> 01:08:33.728
through this millennia of transmission.

01:08:33.728 --> 01:08:36.708
Slowly whatever you do in a particular culture

01:08:36.708 --> 01:08:39.075
it will acquire cultural frills.

01:08:39.075 --> 01:08:42.829
So, one thing is to take off all the cultural frills

01:08:42.829 --> 01:08:44.889
and present it as an absolute science

01:08:44.889 --> 01:08:47.061
and a technology for well-being.

01:08:47.061 --> 01:08:50.165
This is an important thing in an organization like this

01:08:50.165 --> 01:08:52.272
where there are people from every nation,

01:08:52.272 --> 01:08:55.013
there are people from every kind of denominations,

01:08:55.013 --> 01:08:56.930
every kind of faith, every kind of beliefs,

01:08:56.930 --> 01:08:58.024
every kind of ideologies,

01:08:58.024 --> 01:09:02.557
it’s very, very important that yoga is brought as a proper science

01:09:02.557 --> 01:09:04.844
not as a cultural thing,

01:09:04.844 --> 01:09:05.817
not as an Indian thing,

01:09:05.817 --> 01:09:08.167
it’s very important to do that (Applause).

